Halydean Corporation

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Halydean Corporation









Type

Private
(Public listing is pending)


Traded as
NASDAQ: HALY (coming soon)


Industry
Agriculture, Dairy Farming


Founded
1128; 889 years ago (1128)
Kelso, Scotland


Founder
David I of Scotland


Headquarters
Hayward, Wisconsin, U.S.



Key people

Ron Braatz
(President and CEO)
Craig Hunt
(COO)


Products
Milk, Beef, International Trade, Food distribution


Revenue
 US$24 million (2015)


Total assets
 US$159 million (2016)



Number of employees

 80 (2015)


Website
www.halydean.com


Halydean Corporation is a vertically integrated dairy and beef industry consolidation holding company. The company is headquartered in Hayward, Wisconsin, but primarily consists of holdings in subsidiaries. The company CEO is Ron Braatz.[1] The company, a classic rollup, targets dairy facilities for mergers and acquisitions each worth an average $34 million USD, and is moving to increase its revenues from US export sales.[2]



